other_tests.findings: Light pink and slightly turbid cerebrospinal fluid (CSF), with 3090 red cells and 1 white cell per cubic millimeter; protein level was 145 mg per deciliter; glucose 62 mg per deciliter; lactate 1.9 mmol per liter; no organisms seen on Gramâ€™s staining, sterile culture.
Slow conduction velocities consistent with a generalized primary demyelinating sensorimotor polyneuropathy; nearly normal amplitudes, prolonged distal motor latencies.
Very low leukocyte galactosylceramidase activity (0.05 nmol per milligram of protein per hour; reference range, 1 to 8), consistent with Krabbe disease.
